citation.case_name: St. Paul, M. & M. Ry. Co. v. Minnesota

html:
214 U.S. 497

29 S.Ct. 698

53 L.Ed. 1060

ST. PAUL, MINNEAPOLIS, & MANITOBA RAILWAY COMPANY and Great Northern Railway Company, Plaintiffs in Error,
v.
STATE OF MINNESOTA EX REL. CITY OF MINNEAPOLIS.

No. 162.

April 26, 1909.

Messrs. Rome G. Brown, William R. Begg, and Charles S. Albert for plaintiffs in error.

Messrs. Frank Healy and Albert E. Clarke for defendant in error.

Per Curiam:

1

Judgment affirmed on authority of Northern P. R. Co. v. Minnesota, 208 U. S. 583, 52 L. ed. 630, 28 Sup. Ct. Rep. 341.
